# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Firebase Web Config
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com/ and create a project.
# 2. Add a Web App (</> icon) and copy the config values below.
# 3. Copy this file to ".env" (in the same folder) and paste your values.
# 4. Restart `npm run dev` after editing .env so Vite picks it up.
#
# NOTE: Vite only exposes vars prefixed with VITE_ to the browser.
# These keys are safe to ship in client code — security is enforced
# by Firebase Authentication + Firestore Security Rules (see README).

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your-api-key-here
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project-id.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project-id.appspot.com
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=000000000000
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=1:000000000000:web:abcdef1234567890
